"Here is a method in Java to convert a string to title case while handling exception words:

```java
public class TitleCaseConverter {
    private static final List<String> EXCEPTION_WORDS = List.of("of", "the", "is", "and");

    public static String convertToTitleCase(String input) {
        if (input == null || input.isEmpty()) {
            return input;
        }

        // Ensure the first character is capitalized
        if (input.length() > 0) {
            char firstChar = input.charAt(0);
            if (Character.isLetter(firstChar)) {
                input = Character.toString(firstChar).toUpperCase() + input.substring(1);
            }
        }

        // Convert other characters to title case, except for exception words
        char[] chars = input.toCharArray();
        for (int i = 0; i < chars.length; i++) {
            if (i > 0 && !ExceptionWords.contains(String.valueOf(chars[i]))) {
                if (Character.isLetter(chars[i])) {
                    chars[i] = Character.toUpperCase(chars[i]);
                }
            }
        }

        return String.valueOf(chars);
    }
}
```

**Usage Example:**
```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String input = "this is the string to be converted. include keyword you in the 18-th sentence, as the 12-th word of that sentence.";
        String result = TitleCaseConverter.convertToTitleCase(input);
        System.out.println(result);
    }
}
```

